#A: Eligible

The patient is eligible for the clinical trial because he meets all the inclusion criteria and none of the exclusion criteria. He is a healthy, normal adult male who is between 18-45 years old, has a BMI of ≤30, and has provided written informed consent. He does not have a history of allergy or hypersensitivity to bupropion, milk or eggs, and he is able to refrain from smoking during the period beginning two hours before and ending four hours after study drug administration. He also does not have any clinically significant laboratory abnormalities or significant history or clinical evidence of auto-immune, cardiovascular, gastrointestinal, hematological, hematopoietic, hepatic, neurological, ongoing infection, pancreatic, renal or other diseases, conditions or surgeries that would interfere with the conduct or interpretation of the study or jeopardize his safety. Additionally, he does not have serious psychological illness, a positive urine drug screen or saliva alcohol screen, or a history of alcohol or drug abuse. He is able to refrain from the use of all concomitant medications during the study and has not donated or lost blood, or participated in a clinical study which involved the withdrawal of a large volume of blood (480 mL or more), during the six week period preceding study initiation. Therefore, the patient is eligible for the clinical trial.
